14/11/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A Montenegrin Telekom manager has been arrested on suspicion of misappropriating about 1.5m euros, police announced on Saturday (November 13th). 
Slobodan Mandic, logistics and procurement manager, allegedly sold Telekom's pre-paid phone cards without authorisation, for a profit. 
Investigators say he used fake documents in order to get to the cards. 
The scam allegedly ran from December 2008 to May of this year. 
(Tanjug, B92, Pcnen, Srna - 13/11/10)
